as pure as a meteorite's...

32
00:05:15,348 --> 00:05:18,051
such was her bravery and goodness...

33
00:05:18,651 --> 00:05:20,219
she was beloved by nature...

34
00:05:20,787 --> 00:05:22,522
as if she was their daughter.

35
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,635
One fateful night...

36
00:05:36,369 --> 00:05:39,972
the moon blessed her
with an extraordinary gift...

37
00:05:40,373 --> 00:05:42,208
with a tinge of the
magic of the valley...

38
00:05:43,109 --> 00:05:44,143
forever!

39
00:05:45,978 --> 00:05:47,046
The moon power!

40
00:05:51,050 --> 00:05:52,385
From that day forward...

41
00:05:52,752 --> 00:05:53,619
she was known...

42
00:05:53,953 --> 00:05:55,521
as the Moon Princess!

43
00:06:05,465 --> 00:06:08,835
Two ancient families lived in harmony
at the edge of the valley...

44
00:06:09,302 --> 00:06:10,136
sharing nature's bounty.

45
00:06:14,674 --> 00:06:16,376
Daughter to the De Noir clan...

46
00:06:16,576 --> 00:06:18,882
the Moon Princess
was deeply in love

47
00:06:18,883 --> 00:06:21,748
and was to be married
to Sir Wolf Merryweather.

48
00:06:25,151 --> 00:06:25,718
Her father,

49
00:06:26,018 --> 00:06:27,387
Sir William De Noir,

50
00:06:27,787 --> 00:06:31,724
blessed the union by presenting
the couple with a rare black lion.

51
00:06:32,258 --> 00:06:35,061
For my daughter's bridegroom!

52
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:46,038
Thank you, father!

53
00:06:50,510 --> 00:06:54,714
In turn,
Sir Wolf gave his bride a unicorn.

54
00:06:54,747 --> 00:06:57,884
Littered from the
wild white horses of the sea.

55
00:07:01,654 --> 00:07:07,226
Only an animal of such beauty and purity
could be the companion of the Moon Princess.

56
00:07:07,326 --> 00:07:08,728
Her heart overflowed with happiness!

57
00:07:09,662 --> 00:07:13,332
The Moon Princess revealed
the magical powers to both families.

58
00:07:15,001 --> 00:07:18,337
This was found deep
in the heart of the ocean.

59
00:07:18,938 --> 00:07:20,540
This pearl was given to us

60
00:07:20,907 --> 00:07:22,608
by mother nature herself!

61
00:07:23,176 --> 00:07:26,045
Promising untold riches to us all.

62
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:27,713
Look!

63
00:07:28,314 --> 00:07:29,782
They have a unique power!

64
00:07:30,316 --> 00:07:32,585
They can reveal the truth

65
00:07:33,019 --> 00:07:34,220
in man's heart!

66
00:07:34,987 --> 00:07:37,056
Legend told of their unique powers,

67
00:07:37,423 --> 00:07:40,393
so strong the pearls
will grant every wish.

68
00:07:40,493 --> 00:07:42,795
Both good and evil!

69
00:08:04,951 --> 00:08:05,518
Good bye...

70
00:08:07,753 --> 00:08:08,654
Good bye...

71
00:08:08,888 --> 00:08:11,257
You be Miss Maria Merryweather?

72
00:08:12,692 --> 00:08:13,392
My man!

73
00:08:14,126 --> 00:08:14,827
Quick!

74
00:08:18,464 --> 00:08:19,065
Madame...

75
00:08:21,701 --> 00:08:22,702
Get on with you!

76
00:08:24,136 --> 00:08:25,037
Good bye...

77
00:08:25,905 --> 00:08:27,039
yes, yes, yes...

78
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:29,375
Miss Heliotrop?

79
00:08:29,575 --> 00:08:30,243
Maria...

80
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:32,278
When your dear mother died,

81
00:08:32,979 --> 00:08:36,015
I promised her faithfully
that I'll take care of you.

82
00:08:36,582 --> 00:08:39,185
So I'm not going to abandon you now!

83
00:08:39,752 --> 00:08:43,789
If you're going to live with your uncle,
or in the middle of the country-side,

84
00:08:44,190 --> 00:08:45,558
then I shall be there with you.

85
00:09:13,386 --> 00:09:15,254
Where are my charcoal tablets?

86
00:09:15,621 --> 00:09:17,890
These are doing nothing
for my indigestion.

87
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:28,367
How can I possibly go
live in the country?

88
00:09:29,168 --> 00:09:31,737
It's like a camp-site!

89
00:09:38,311 --> 00:09:40,713
Maria, there's only one thing
that can save us now.

90
00:09:41,047 --> 00:09:41,881
Clever girl,

91
00:09:42,014 --> 00:09:42,715
French,

92
00:09:43,015 --> 00:09:44,083
needle point.

93
00:10:12,011 --> 00:10:13,012
What's happening?

94
00:10:13,546 --> 00:10:14,246
Have we arrived?

95
00:10:16,582 --> 00:10:18,084
Is he deaf or something?

96
00:10:19,185 --> 00:10:20,820
The man is obviously a half wit.

97
00:10:47,279 --> 00:10:47,947
Who are they?

98
00:10:48,014 --> 00:10:49,148
What do they want?

99
00:10:49,248 --> 00:10:50,616
Don't worry my dear,

100
00:10:50,816 --> 00:10:52,451
Sir Benjamin will protect us, I'm sure!

101
00:11:17,176 --> 00:11:17,843
Miss...

102
00:11:29,155 --> 00:11:30,289
Welcome to Moonacre!

103
00:11:39,031 --> 00:11:40,633
Unfortunate circumstances.

104
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:43,703
There we are, nothing to be done.

105
00:11:47,173 --> 00:11:49,108
I'm pleased to meet you, Uncle.

106
00:11:50,643 --> 00:11:51,577
Miss Heliotrop.

107
00:11:52,278 --> 00:11:53,212
Oh, Sir Benjamin.

108
00:11:53,713 --> 00:11:54,980
Oh, what a journey we had!!!

109
00:11:55,815 --> 00:11:58,217
Not one hour from this
very door we were accosted by

110
00:11:58,584 --> 00:11:59,351
a bunch of ruffians.

111
00:11:59,585 --> 00:12:00,985
Madame, please!
- It...

112
00:12:00,986 --> 00:12:03,522
Tell me your fascinating story
some other time if I may.

113
00:12:30,549 --> 00:12:31,784
His name is Wolf.

114
00:12:33,753 --> 00:12:35,321
There are those
who find him alarming.

115
00:12:35,621 --> 00:12:36,989
He can kill in an instant.

116
00:12:38,457 --> 00:12:39,391
But you're a Merryweather.

117
00:12:40,793 --> 00:12:42,394
He very probably won't harm you.

118
00:12:58,210 --> 00:13:00,746
Miss Heliotrop,
your room is over there to the right.

119
00:13:01,380 --> 00:13:02,782
Oh, thank you, Sir Benjamin.

120
00:13:05,551 --> 00:13:06,685
Well, come along Maria.

121
00:13:07,019 --> 00:13:08,888
I'm sure that your room...
will be next to mine.

122
00:13:09,088 --> 00:13:10,790
No, Maria's room is up in the tower.

123
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:12,725
But, I'm kind...

124
00:13:12,892 --> 00:13:14,338
You have to inspect the room first

125
00:13:14,339 --> 00:13:15,961
before you turn your
nose up at whatever it is.

126
00:13:33,078 --> 00:13:34,380
Good night, Uncle!

127
00:13:36,582 --> 00:13:37,850
Charmed, I'm sure.

128
00:15:53,185 --> 00:15:54,653
What on earth is this?

129
00:15:59,291 --> 00:16:00,092
Oh, no!

130
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:02,328
No, I think not.

131
00:16:38,597 --> 00:16:39,465
Young lady.

132
00:16:40,766 --> 00:16:42,101
We're taking breakfast in here.

133
00:16:44,303 --> 00:16:45,337
Where did you get this from?

134
00:16:46,505 --> 00:16:47,940
Oh um, papa left it to me.

135
00:16:50,042 --> 00:16:51,543
Well, he had no right...

136
00:16:52,277 --> 00:16:53,112
This belong here.

137
00:16:55,714 --> 00:16:56,782
But, that's mine!!

138
00:17:01,420 --> 00:17:02,521
Miss Heliotrop!

139
00:17:03,555 --> 00:17:04,256
Help!

140
00:17:04,456 --> 00:17:07,026
Help, tell him he can't
take my father's book from me!

141
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:08,460
Maria!

142
00:17:09,361 --> 00:17:11,797
Good question!
Why don't you just speak...

143
00:17:11,897 --> 00:17:12,931
That he can't just go and...

144
00:17:13,165 --> 00:17:13,866
Maria!

145
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:15,567
Don't worry.

146
00:17:15,634 --> 00:17:17,770
I'm sure that he's just keeping
it safe somewhere for you.

147
00:17:17,836 --> 00:17:19,371
Sit down.
Have your porridge.

148
00:17:19,872 --> 00:17:20,472
Miss.

149
00:17:32,017 --> 00:17:34,286
There be your breakfast, Miss.

150
00:17:41,860 --> 00:17:44,730
Maria, you really must
try this delicious omelet.

151
00:17:45,030 --> 00:17:48,500
Hum,um, a dish best
enjoyed in silence, I'm told.

152
00:18:01,780 --> 00:18:05,217
Uncle, when can you return
my father's book to me?

153
00:18:16,528 --> 00:18:17,429
Now,

154
00:18:17,663 --> 00:18:20,262
you certainly have a very,
very good cook, Sir Benjamin.

155
00:18:20,263 --> 00:18:21,767
Have you... have you had her long?

156
00:18:22,234 --> 00:18:25,003
Madame, no woman has stepped
in this house for years!

157
00:18:25,370 --> 00:18:28,707
And believe me,
the silence has been blissful.

158
00:18:33,745 --> 00:18:38,080
Now, I must say, this country food is
doing wonders for my trapped wind!

159
00:18:39,218 --> 00:18:42,888
Madame, please! Can't a man enjoy
a meal in his own home in silence?

160
00:18:53,432 --> 00:18:54,465
Well, do tell us Uncle...

161
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:58,670
Why did you invite such
irritating and noisy females

162
00:18:58,871 --> 00:19:00,806
into your nice quiet house?

163
00:19:01,306 --> 00:19:02,407
I'd love to know.

164
00:19:04,042 --> 00:19:07,880
My useless brother died in debt
and it fell on me to take you in.

165
00:19:08,247 --> 00:19:10,849
The man was a... cowardly
good for nothing.

166
00:19:11,049 --> 00:19:11,950
Sir Benjamin!!

167
00:19:12,251 --> 00:19:13,886
How dare you say that?!

168
00:19:14,119 --> 00:19:15,654
My father was a Colonel!

169
00:19:15,687 --> 00:19:16,421
Yes.

170
00:19:16,688 --> 00:19:19,391
And he died in debt owing money
to half the regiment.

171
00:19:19,591 --> 00:19:20,993
He fought for his country!

172
00:19:21,260 --> 00:19:23,929
And got himself killed
in a backstreet gambling den.

173
00:19:24,930 --> 00:19:27,799
Borrowed money once too many times
from the wrong sort of money lenders.

174
00:19:30,435 --> 00:19:32,137
He wouldn't take money from me,
would he?

175
00:19:33,305 --> 00:19:33,638
Oh no.

176
00:19:33,972 --> 00:19:36,775
Damn, all his pride.

177
00:19:37,709 --> 00:19:39,645
You're a Merryweather, Maria...

178
00:19:40,212 --> 00:19:43,048
And this is where you belong.
Here, at Moonacre.

179
00:19:44,583 --> 00:19:45,417
There we are.

180
00:19:45,984 --> 00:19:47,052
Nothing else to be done.

181
00:19:51,290 --> 00:19:54,526
Library is private
and my study prohibited.

182
00:19:58,096 --> 00:19:59,298
And in here...

183
00:20:00,899 --> 00:20:02,734
The East wing, closed...

184
00:20:02,901 --> 00:20:04,603
the West wing, out of bounds.

185
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:05,604
There we are.

186
00:20:06,104 --> 00:20:08,106
- And here...
- Uncle, about that attack yesterday.

187
00:20:08,473 --> 00:20:09,708
Can't something be done?

188
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:11,410
Yes... keep your little nose out.

189
00:20:12,010 --> 00:20:12,778
I beg your pardon?

190
00:20:12,978 --> 00:20:14,880
Just keep out of the forest.

191
00:20:15,814 --> 00:20:17,082
But why?
Who are they?

192
00:20:17,649 --> 00:20:21,220
There's a band of ruffians in the woods.
The De Noir clan.

193
00:20:22,054 --> 00:20:24,022
You mean like the "De Noir"
from the story book?

194
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:25,324
No, no, no... these are real enough.

195
00:20:25,791 --> 00:20:28,360
Poachers, bandits, plunderers, robbers.

196
00:20:29,595 --> 00:20:30,095
Ladies.

197
00:20:30,896 --> 00:20:32,331
This should suit your needs.

198
00:20:34,132 --> 00:20:36,101
And this will be your classroom.

199
00:20:44,943 --> 00:20:47,977
(Speaking French)

200
00:23:14,726 --> 00:23:17,894
Digweed...
Bring me my whip.

201
00:23:19,498 --> 00:23:21,600
You weren't expecting me to...

202
00:23:22,033 --> 00:23:23,468
She can ride, can she?

203
00:23:23,635 --> 00:23:24,970
Oh, Sir Benjamin,
it's a matter of fact

204
00:23:24,971 --> 00:23:26,738
that a lady should never be
allowed to sit on a horse!

205
00:23:26,972 --> 00:23:31,042
They're unstable and
they're vicious creatures.

206
00:23:40,952 --> 00:23:45,390
I think, Sir Benjamin, it might be an
appropriate moment for me to retire.

207
00:23:47,559 --> 00:23:48,627
Take care!

208
00:23:50,395 --> 00:23:52,664
Come, Maria.

209
00:23:52,831 --> 00:23:54,132
Every Merryweather rides.

210
00:23:54,866 --> 00:23:56,301
It's in the blood.

211
00:23:56,668 --> 00:24:01,373
This is Peririco... she's a little
feisty but she's a loyal stead.

212
00:24:01,606 --> 00:24:02,974
Just hold out your hand.

213
00:24:04,309 --> 00:24:05,544
I give you my word,

214
00:24:05,977 --> 00:24:08,346
it'll stay attached to you, Miss.

215
00:24:38,410 --> 00:24:39,945
You see, Miss?

216
00:24:40,512 --> 00:24:41,546
She knows.

217
00:24:53,692 --> 00:24:56,561
- You're getting on well with Peririco...
- Yes, Uncle.

218
00:25:03,969 --> 00:25:05,270
We should be heading back.

219
00:25:05,437 --> 00:25:06,271
It's getting late.

220
00:25:11,309 --> 00:25:15,146
Uncle, I'm really enjoying this.
Could I stay out a little longer?

221
00:25:17,048 --> 00:25:19,818
As long as you promise to stay
within the Moonacre boundary.

222
00:25:20,719 --> 00:25:21,353
Remember...

223
00:25:21,786 --> 00:25:25,290
I can only vouch for your safety
if you stay out of the forest.

224
00:25:26,091 --> 00:25:27,726
I will be home before long,

225
00:25:27,792 --> 00:25:29,995
and Peririco will take good care of me.

226
00:25:31,229 --> 00:25:31,963
Very well.

227
00:25:35,734 --> 00:25:36,568
Goodbye Uncle!

228
00:25:49,614 --> 00:25:52,150
What's so special
about the forest anyway?

229
00:26:03,795 --> 00:26:04,963
You stay here.

230
00:26:19,811 --> 00:26:21,246
Oh, little baby.

231
00:26:21,313 --> 00:26:23,281
Who did this to you?

232
00:26:26,751 --> 00:26:29,721
One catch two captives.

233
00:26:30,088 --> 00:26:31,256
What do you want?

234
00:26:34,025 --> 00:26:36,861
Let's go. Catch an animal that
comes to get you coming to help!

235
00:26:37,195 --> 00:26:37,963
I know who you are!

236
00:26:38,330 --> 00:26:39,965
You're bandits and plunderers!

237
00:26:47,339 --> 00:26:48,306
You!

238
00:26:48,740 --> 00:26:49,941
You're coming with us now!

239
00:26:50,308 --> 00:26:53,578
My father's just dying
to make your acquaintance.

240
00:26:57,382 --> 00:26:58,883
It's the demon dog!

241
00:27:12,364 --> 00:27:14,632
Thank you,
you obedient doggy!

242
00:27:16,368 --> 00:27:17,602
Come on, little one...

243
00:27:17,969 --> 00:27:19,070
Let me take you home.

244
00:27:30,749 --> 00:27:32,550
Robin, it's your father!

245
00:27:40,258 --> 00:27:45,764
What did I do to deserve
such a prize filth for a son?

246
00:28:05,116 --> 00:28:08,086
I hope Peririco gave you an
educational tour of the estate.

247
00:28:10,655 --> 00:28:12,624
I have a wounded hare.

248
00:28:13,892 --> 00:28:17,062
That, young lady,
is a rare Moonacre rabbit.

249
00:28:17,595 --> 00:28:20,498
By far the most beautiful,
brave and serene creature.

250
00:28:20,932 --> 00:28:22,963
And as you've brought
her in from the wild,

251
00:28:22,964 --> 00:28:24,302
she's now your responsibility.

252
00:28:25,036 --> 00:28:26,369
And with your knowledge of animals,

253
00:28:26,370 --> 00:28:28,273
I very much doubt it will
live to see the morning.

254
00:28:30,308 --> 00:28:32,577
Keep out of the forest child!

255
00:28:33,912 --> 00:28:34,546
Maria?

256
00:28:36,247 --> 00:28:37,615
Goodness gracious!

257
00:28:38,116 --> 00:28:38,383
Look at your...

258
00:28:39,918 --> 00:28:40,685
dress!

259
00:28:46,057 --> 00:28:48,026
Maria, there's something
alive on your body!

260
00:28:48,660 --> 00:28:51,296
Miss Heliotrop, please calm down!

261
00:28:52,063 --> 00:28:53,698
This is a Moonacre rabbit...

262
00:28:54,666 --> 00:28:57,736
A beautiful, brave and serene creature.

263
00:28:58,570 --> 00:29:00,004
I intend to look after it.

264
00:29:03,875 --> 00:29:05,710
And I'm going to call her Serena.

265
00:29:53,458 --> 00:29:54,025
Uncle?

266
00:29:54,592 --> 00:29:57,996
I really think you and I
have some matters to discuss.

267
00:29:59,397 --> 00:30:02,000
There are some very strange things
going on in this house.

268
00:30:02,267 --> 00:30:06,304
First off, who always keeps my dress
and leaves the biscuits in my room?

269
00:30:07,172 --> 00:30:08,473
The stars on my ceiling move.

270
00:30:08,873 --> 00:30:10,642
There's a mysterious
white horse outside.

271
00:30:11,609 --> 00:30:14,448
This place is falling apart,
things appear to move,

272
00:30:14,449 --> 00:30:16,414
and the piano plays
music on its own!

273
00:30:17,248 --> 00:30:19,350
I mean, I have never even
seen the kitchen.

274
00:30:19,717 --> 00:30:21,486
So where on earth
does all this food come from?

275
00:30:21,786 --> 00:30:24,222
Do you ever stop asking questions?

276
00:30:29,828 --> 00:30:31,529
Uncle, I...

277
00:30:35,867 --> 00:30:37,168
Sit down, my dear.

278
00:30:41,973 --> 00:30:43,006
Wolf?

279
00:30:46,778 --> 00:30:47,779
Where are we going?

280
00:30:58,823 --> 00:30:59,957
Wolf?

281
00:31:02,093 --> 00:31:02,694
Wolf?

282
00:31:04,162 --> 00:31:04,195
Wolf?!

283
00:31:33,224 --> 00:31:37,128
Marmaduke Scarlet.
Chef of all chefs,

284
00:31:38,062 --> 00:31:40,164
at your service, Little Princess.

285
00:31:51,976 --> 00:31:53,177
How do you do that?

286
00:31:53,578 --> 00:31:55,346
Get me some sherbet, will you?

287
00:31:55,813 --> 00:31:57,181
Chop, chop...

288
00:31:59,317 --> 00:32:01,486
I'm not actually really sure
where your sherbet is...

289
00:32:01,653 --> 00:32:04,622
Never you mind...I'll get it...

290
00:32:09,928 --> 00:32:13,097
Are you the one who leaves
the milk and biscuits for me?

291
00:32:18,069 --> 00:32:22,740
These past few days,
it all comes back to me.

292
00:32:41,759 --> 00:32:44,862
Scarlet please, will you stop
yourself for just one moment?

293
00:32:45,863 --> 00:32:48,800
Surely somebody in this household
must be able to answer my questions.

294
00:32:49,233 --> 00:32:51,502
Dear Princess, a little bit of magic...

295
00:32:51,970 --> 00:32:53,805
has come back to the valley.

296
00:32:54,505 --> 00:32:58,309
You obviously haven't
finished reading the book.

297
00:33:00,979 --> 00:33:01,946
The book?

298
00:33:03,748 --> 00:33:05,350
But my uncle took it
away from me.

299
00:33:07,652 --> 00:33:08,553
In the library,

300
00:33:10,355 --> 00:33:14,993
you'll find a slim volume,
Secret Doors and Private Lockers...

301
00:33:15,460 --> 00:33:16,594
Perhaps a piece of...

302
00:33:17,428 --> 00:33:20,698
stargazer pie for your study.

303
00:34:31,736 --> 00:34:34,772
The Moon Princess truly believed
in the goodness of all.

304
00:34:36,207 --> 00:34:39,377
But the men soon fell to the greed
that was in their heart.

305
00:34:40,111 --> 00:34:43,781
Each desperate to claim
the power of the pearls for himself.

306
00:34:47,418 --> 00:34:49,020
We are the chosen ones!

307
00:34:50,188 --> 00:34:54,459
These pearls stay with
the De Noir clan forever!

308
00:34:55,526 --> 00:34:55,893
Father?

309
00:34:56,794 --> 00:34:57,962
Come! Be with me.

310
00:34:58,429 --> 00:35:01,366
Let Moonacre be your home
and be your family.

311
00:35:01,432 --> 00:35:03,367
Speak true!

312
00:35:05,736 --> 00:35:10,374
With the power of these pearls,
I can claim the valley for myself.

313
00:35:11,609 --> 00:35:12,944
No.

314
00:35:13,177 --> 00:35:17,048
Together, I mean together
we could rule the valley.

315
00:35:18,583 --> 00:35:20,685
These pearls belongs to no man,

316
00:35:20,852 --> 00:35:22,687
they belong to nature!

317
00:35:23,621 --> 00:35:24,822
Give it to me!!

318
00:35:25,056 --> 00:35:26,090
No! Give them to me!!!

319
00:35:30,128 --> 00:35:30,561
No no no!!!

320
00:35:30,628 --> 00:35:32,363
I beg of you... please!!!

321
00:35:32,597 --> 00:35:35,133
You cannot let your heart
be ruled by greed!

322
00:35:36,901 --> 00:35:39,303
Betrayed by those she loved the most,

323
00:35:39,504 --> 00:35:43,107
the Moon Princess unleashed
the power bestowed upon her,

324
00:35:43,541 --> 00:35:46,911
and cast a terrifying
curse over them all.

325
00:35:47,879 --> 00:35:49,213
Hear me!!!!

326
00:35:49,614 --> 00:35:52,049
You've gone against the nature,

327
00:35:52,350 --> 00:35:54,752
and you shall suffer for it!

328
00:35:54,952 --> 00:35:59,257
Nature will wreak her revenge
and put a curse upon this valley.

329
00:35:59,557 --> 00:36:00,424
One day,

330
00:36:00,825 --> 00:36:03,294
a pure heart will walk among you.

331
00:36:03,594 --> 00:36:05,363
If she can't lift the curse,

332
00:36:05,796 --> 00:36:08,933
when the 5000th moon
rises from the sea,

333
00:36:09,367 --> 00:36:14,405
this valley shall be plunged
into eternal darkness!!!!

334
00:36:18,342 --> 00:36:20,244
The moon pearls vanished that day,

335
00:36:20,611 --> 00:36:22,947
and where to find them
remained a secret.

336
00:36:23,548 --> 00:36:26,050
Marmaduke!
The house... the valley... it's all...

337
00:36:27,752 --> 00:36:28,920
- Cursed!

338
00:36:30,188 --> 00:36:31,122
Oh yes!

339
00:36:32,690 --> 00:36:33,991
Take a look around you.

340
00:36:35,193 --> 00:36:38,262
Everything's falling apart.

341
00:36:39,964 --> 00:36:41,766
Ever since that terrible day,

342
00:36:42,233 --> 00:36:45,069
the two families have
been totally consumed

343
00:36:45,736 --> 00:36:46,737
with pride...

344
00:36:47,505 --> 00:36:48,973
and blind hatred.

345
00:36:52,710 --> 00:36:55,613
And the only person
who can break this curse

346
00:36:56,414 --> 00:36:59,183
is a true Moon Princess!

347
00:36:59,217 --> 00:37:00,451
The Moon Princess?

348
00:37:01,452 --> 00:37:02,220
But...

349
00:37:02,587 --> 00:37:04,121
she lived hundreds of years ago.

350
00:37:04,355 --> 00:37:07,391
The legend tells...
of a little white horse,

351
00:37:07,758 --> 00:37:10,428
a mystical companion
to protect her.

352
00:37:10,561 --> 00:37:11,662
A magical creature...

353
00:37:12,129 --> 00:37:15,132
invisible so they say...
to anyone...

354
00:37:15,533 --> 00:37:18,002
except a true Moon Princess.

355
00:37:19,570 --> 00:37:20,571
You mean...

356
00:37:21,372 --> 00:37:24,141
I'm suppose to be this...

357
00:37:25,409 --> 00:37:28,312
I'm supposed to undo this curse?

358
00:37:28,479 --> 00:37:29,847
Everyone knows the legend.

359
00:37:30,014 --> 00:37:32,183
Peace will never be restored...

360
00:37:32,383 --> 00:37:36,220
until the pearls are return to the sea
and the families reunited!

361
00:37:36,487 --> 00:37:38,256
This is all madness!

362
00:37:41,692 --> 00:37:45,129
Time is slipping away.

363
00:37:45,429 --> 00:37:47,298
the 5,000th moon...

364
00:37:47,531 --> 00:37:49,100
to set it right.

365
