415
00:42:38,789 --> 00:42:40,024
But there is nowhere to hide.

416
00:42:40,457 --> 00:42:43,093
He sent you here
because he loved you.

417
00:42:43,294 --> 00:42:45,863
Because Moonacre
is where you belong.

418
00:42:49,900 --> 00:42:51,468
You and I are the same.

419
00:42:54,004 --> 00:42:55,372
Except...

420
00:42:56,540 --> 00:42:57,741
Except?

421
00:42:59,176 --> 00:43:02,379
Where I failed,
you might succeed.

422
00:43:03,280 --> 00:43:06,650
What about my uncle?
Sir Benjamin... can't he help?

423
00:43:07,318 --> 00:43:11,055
Never, ever mention that man to me again,
do you understand?

424
00:43:13,691 --> 00:43:15,559
Your past is behind you.

425
00:43:16,727 --> 00:43:19,730
Your future awaits you
if you want it.

426
00:43:20,531 --> 00:43:21,966
You decide.

427
00:43:22,900 --> 00:43:24,301
I want to help.

428
00:43:24,535 --> 00:43:27,171
I just don't know what
I'm supposed to do to begin.

429
00:43:27,438 --> 00:43:28,872
Find the pearls!

430
00:43:29,073 --> 00:43:30,641
Nobody knows where they are.

431
00:43:30,874 --> 00:43:33,210
Each family blames the other
for taking them.

432
00:43:36,380 --> 00:43:37,881
They are both to blame.

433
00:43:38,549 --> 00:43:41,785
The De Noir took the casket
then we must have the key.

434
00:43:52,429 --> 00:43:53,564
The key!

435
00:44:05,676 --> 00:44:06,644
Now for the casket.

436
00:44:06,710 --> 00:44:08,345
You have to take me there.

437
00:44:08,479 --> 00:44:10,614
- Where?
- To De Noir.

438
00:44:10,881 --> 00:44:12,650
You've to take me
to where they live.

439
00:44:23,694 --> 00:44:25,295
There it is!

440
00:44:27,798 --> 00:44:30,267
Loveday...
are you alright?

441
00:44:31,969 --> 00:44:35,205
I'm sorry!
I can never go back there!

442
00:44:38,809 --> 00:44:40,010
Loveday!

443
00:44:40,711 --> 00:44:41,745
Loveday!

444
00:46:19,409 --> 00:46:21,845
Father, I could pad and place a scythe
and nail it under their roof.

445
00:46:22,312 --> 00:46:25,582
Don't go near Moonacre...
that house is damned!

446
00:46:26,049 --> 00:46:28,185
No...
the word is...

447
00:46:28,752 --> 00:46:31,622
she is about to meet her downfall.

448
00:46:46,937 --> 00:46:50,440
How kind of you to join us,
Moon Princess.

449
00:46:54,745 --> 00:46:57,080
Oh...
Oh, and what is this?

450
00:46:57,981 --> 00:47:01,385
She has brought us
the lost key, gentlemen!

451
00:47:02,386 --> 00:47:06,374
Wasn't it terrible of the De Noir
to have the moon pearls

452
00:47:06,375 --> 00:47:09,193
hidden up here all the time...
haven't we?

453
00:47:09,860 --> 00:47:11,829
Well, it's true isn't it?

454
00:47:11,929 --> 00:47:13,864
Your ancestors stole them!

455
00:47:14,031 --> 00:47:15,933
My ancestors?!

456
00:47:17,067 --> 00:47:19,403
Well, perhaps Princess...

457
00:47:19,937 --> 00:47:21,905
I should introduce you...

458
00:47:25,209 --> 00:47:29,580
Maria Merryweather...
the last Moon Princess.

459
00:47:30,480 --> 00:47:31,682
Sir William.

460
00:47:33,183 --> 00:47:36,153
The very first De Noir.

461
00:47:42,826 --> 00:47:44,228
The pearls casket!

462
00:47:44,528 --> 00:47:48,699
And you so very kindly
brought us the key.

463
00:47:56,173 --> 00:47:57,241
You've hidden them!!

464
00:47:57,541 --> 00:48:00,210
They were never there, girl!

465
00:48:00,878 --> 00:48:04,114
